'''Otto Pettersonfjellet''' is a mountain in [[Nathorst Land]] at [[Spitsbergen]], [[Svalbard]]. It extends over a length of about seven kilometers, and its highest peak is 1,076 [[m.a.s.l.]] It is named after Swedish oceanographer Sven Otto Petterson.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Otto_Pettersonfjellet |title=Otto Pettersonfjellet (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=24 February 2015}}</ref> The glacier of [[Storvolbreen]] is situated between Otto Pettersonfjellet and [[Storvola]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Storvolbreen |title=Storvolbreen (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=24 February 2015}}</ref> and [[Tarmbreen]] separates Otto Pettersonfjellet from [[Glof<U+00F8>ykja]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://placenames.npolar.no/stadnamn/Tarmbreen |title=Tarmbreen (Svalbard) |publisher=[[Norwegian Polar Institute]] |accessdate=24 February 2015}}</ref>

